From d9e04ae3567f7018efbb4d3b4463ba4befcb8668 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Thomas Zimmermann <tzimmermann@suse.de>
Date: Wed, 8 Apr 2020 10:26:40 +0200
Subject: drm/vboxvideo: Set up fbdev after registering device; remove error
 checks
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit
Git-commit: 3662cd199266a95b3d649bbe6054094c610817fe
Patch-mainline: v5.8-rc1
References: jsc#SLE-12680, jsc#SLE-12880, jsc#SLE-12882, jsc#SLE-12883, jsc#SLE-13496, jsc#SLE-15322

Generic fbdev support is a DRM client. Set it up after registering
the new DRM device. Remove the error checks as the driver's probe
function should not depend on a DRM client's state.

Signed-off-by: Thomas Zimmermann <tzimmermann@suse.de>
Reviewed-by: Noralf Tr√∏nnes <noralf@tronnes.org>
Acked-by: Sam Ravnborg <sam@ravnborg.org>
Acked-by: Gerd Hoffmann <kraxel@redhat.com>
Link: https://patchwork.freedesktop.org/patch/msgid/20200408082641.590-10-tzimmermann@suse.de
Signed-off-by: Patrik Jakobsson <pjakobsson@suse.de>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/vboxvideo/vbox_drv.c | 6 ++----
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/vboxvideo/vbox_drv.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/vboxvideo/vbox_drv.c
index d685ec197fa0..282348e071fe 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/vboxvideo/vbox_drv.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/vboxvideo/vbox_drv.c
@@ -82,14 +82,12 @@ static int vbox_pci_probe(struct pci_dev *pdev, const struct pci_device_id *ent)
 	if (ret)
 		goto err_mode_fini;
 
-	ret = drm_fbdev_generic_setup(&vbox->ddev, 32);
-	if (ret)
-		goto err_irq_fini;
-
 	ret = drm_dev_register(&vbox->ddev, 0);
 	if (ret)
 		goto err_irq_fini;
 
+	drm_fbdev_generic_setup(&vbox->ddev, 32);
+
 	return 0;
 
 err_irq_fini:
